<i> </i>

23
00:01:56,694 --> 00:01:58,982
Traditional Tonjiru (¥600), Beer (¥600), Sake (¥500), Shochu (¥400)
Max. three drinks per customer
<i>My menu is all there.</i>

24
00:01:58,982 --> 00:01:59,896
Traditional Tonjiru (¥600), Beer (¥600), Sake (¥500), Shochu (¥400)
Max. three drinks per customer
<i>The possibility of getting served anything else...</i>

25
00:01:59,896 --> 00:02:01,436
<i>The possibility of getting served anything else...</i>

26
00:02:02,006 --> 00:02:04,116
<i>as long as it's possible,</i>

27
00:02:04,233 --> 00:02:07,253
<i>my business model.</i>

28
00:02:07,666 --> 00:02:13,106
<i>I am open from midnight
to seven of the morning after.</i>

29
00:02:13,328 --> 00:02:14,295
<i>People call this...</i>

30
00:02:14,403 --> 00:02:16,583
<i>Midnight Restaurant.</i>

31
00:02:17,730 --> 00:02:19,455
<i>How is business doing?!</i>

32
00:02:19,886 --> 00:02:22,066
<i>Well enough, I'd say.</i>

33
00:02:24,449 --> 00:02:27,400
~ SHINYA SHOKUDO ~
Midnight Restaurant

34
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:32,748
<i>(*Fried pork cutlet, onions, and egg over rice)</i>
Episode 6
Katsudon*

35
00:02:38,579 --> 00:02:41,999
So that's what I
told you, just be honest.

36
00:02:42,482 --> 00:02:43,641
Will it be all right?

37
00:02:43,666 --> 00:02:45,015
Of course it will!

38
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:48,162
He's always honest
and to the point, right?

39
00:02:48,187 --> 00:02:49,307
Right.

40
00:02:49,332 --> 00:02:52,728
Chu-san, can I
have my tamagoyaki back?

41
00:02:52,753 --> 00:02:54,172
Ohh...

42
00:02:55,249 --> 00:02:58,629
He should be here by now?!

43
00:02:59,116 --> 00:03:01,906
Wow... Tasty!
This stock is just killer.

44
00:03:02,096 --> 00:03:04,204
Here you go, divided in half.

45
00:03:04,229 --> 00:03:06,209
Nice!
Where is this from?

46
00:03:06,327 --> 00:03:09,099
Hm... From the mart down the corner.

47
00:03:09,447 --> 00:03:12,550
<i>(*Eastern Hokkaido province)</i>
For Atka mackerels, the ones
from Rausu in Shiretoko* are the best.

48
00:03:12,575 --> 00:03:15,815
Wow... You sure know a
lot about mackerel, don't you?

49
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:17,931
I've always liked fish
ever since I was little.

50
00:03:17,956 --> 00:03:19,546
Bon apetit.

51
00:03:23,429 --> 00:03:24,889
Yummy!

52
00:03:25,090 --> 00:03:26,945
We need to go right after you're done.

53
00:03:26,970 --> 00:03:28,700
You should be asleep by now.

54
00:03:31,043 --> 00:03:32,908
Good evening.

55
00:03:32,933 --> 00:03:37,153
Ohh! Testosterone is
starting to fill the air now!

56
00:03:37,679 --> 00:03:40,168
Today was a big day for me.

57
00:03:40,193 --> 00:03:42,295
Master, can I order something?

58
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:43,310
Yeah...

59
00:03:43,853 --> 00:03:46,313
Here... Kill the thirst with this.

60
00:03:46,338 --> 00:03:47,938
Thanks.

61
00:03:49,100 --> 00:03:50,760
- Here.
- Thank you!

62
00:03:53,376 --> 00:03:56,528
Ahh... It's great.

63
00:03:56,553 --> 00:04:00,632
0:32 of Round 8,
a killer KO punch.

64
00:04:00,657 --> 00:04:02,137
How did you know?

65
00:04:02,578 --> 00:04:05,465
He was at the match,
and told him the finish.

66
00:04:05,490 --> 00:04:07,530
And he didn't even ask for it, right?

67
00:04:10,330 --> 00:04:11,580
Thank you very much.

68
00:04:11,983 --> 00:04:12,961
Ahh... It was just...

69
00:04:12,986 --> 00:04:16,197
Don't just sit there
mumbling, and ask him!

70
00:04:16,503 --> 00:04:21,515
Ahh... I was wondering...
whether you would like...

71
00:04:21,540 --> 00:04:23,631
You know, your photos.

72
00:04:23,656 --> 00:04:25,854
Of you training at
the gym, for instance.

73
00:04:25,879 --> 00:04:28,375
Could I give it a shot?

74
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:30,528
He just got started in that field,

75
00:04:30,553 --> 00:04:34,833
but he always says he wants
to publish a photobook with a boxer.

76
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:39,180
Will it be all right,
using someone like me...

77
00:04:39,776 --> 00:04:41,064
Thank you very much.

78
00:04:41,089 --> 00:04:42,699
I'm counting on you.

79
00:04:44,216 --> 00:04:46,900
Here... A toast.
Let's have one.

80
00:05:07,353 --> 00:05:10,505
<i>(*Middle-aged man (lit. Uncle))</i>
Oji-san*, what
happened to your face?

81
00:05:10,530 --> 00:05:11,838
Mayu...

82
00:05:11,863 --> 00:05:13,943
I'm sorry.

83
00:05:15,330 --> 00:05:18,361
I'm a boxer.

84
00:05:18,386 --> 00:05:21,083
Is that something like K-1?

85
00:05:21,410 --> 00:05:25,880
It's a tad different...

86
00:05:26,060 --> 00:05:27,720
You know the sport well?

87
00:05:27,860 --> 00:05:30,922
<i>(*combat sports*)
She's a huge kakutogi* fan.

88
00:05:31,436 --> 00:05:33,851
Every time he wins a bout,

89
00:05:33,876 --> 00:05:36,266
Kat-chan comes
here to eat katsudon.

90
00:05:36,423 --> 00:05:39,155
Ahh... His name is
Kawada Katsutoshi.

91
00:05:39,180 --> 00:05:40,610
Be nice to him.

92
00:05:41,563 --> 00:05:43,323
Looks tasty...

93
00:05:43,348 --> 00:05:45,408
Master. Give me
one as well, nuki-style.

94
00:05:45,781 --> 00:05:47,011
Nuki?!

95
00:05:47,036 --> 00:05:48,978
Means without rice.

96
00:05:49,003 --> 00:05:50,279
I see...

97
00:05:50,633 --> 00:05:52,453
Mom, did you know that?

98
00:05:53,123 --> 00:05:55,223
<i>I'll get a double one
with rice.</i>

99
00:05:55,600 --> 00:05:57,736
<i>You can just call it
a normal "double katsudon."</i>

100
00:05:57,761 --> 00:05:59,491
<i>Is that so?</i>

101
00:06:30,310 --> 00:06:34,300
You'll pardon me,
but we're open from midnight.

102
00:06:34,630 --> 00:06:37,980
Because it's a "Midnight
Restaurant," I guess?!

103
00:06:40,513 --> 00:06:41,833
Brought you an invitation,

104
00:06:41,950 --> 00:06:44,040
to Komichi-san's exhibition.

105
00:06:46,646 --> 00:06:48,161
He's doing it at a
tavern in Golden Street,

106
00:06:48,161 --> 00:06:50,574
and I'm touring the
neighborhood to give out invitations.

107
00:06:50,790 --> 00:06:52,170
Komichi-kun?

108
00:06:52,953 --> 00:06:54,953
He's spending all day at the gym.

109
00:06:55,242 --> 00:06:59,546
Not just me, he's shooting photos
of all the other boxers at the gym.

110
00:06:59,826 --> 00:07:02,401
Will twenty invitations be enough?

111
00:07:02,426 --> 00:07:06,436
Earlier on, Akemi-chan
and Mayu-chan came by.

112
00:07:08,707 --> 00:07:10,127
Ohh...

113
00:07:11,513 --> 00:07:13,092
K-1?

114
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:15,718
Looks like they saw your last bout,

115
00:07:15,743 --> 00:07:21,619
and came here asking for katsudon.

116
00:07:23,370 --> 00:07:25,060
Really?

117
00:07:25,760 --> 00:07:28,531
Then, next time they come by,
tell them I'll treat them.

118
00:07:28,556 --> 00:07:30,746
How about you tell them yourself?

119
00:07:30,903 --> 00:07:34,643
Akemi-chan works
at a snack bar nearby.

120
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:38,380
She'll probably be there tonight.

121
00:07:39,210 --> 00:07:40,200
Forget it.

122
00:07:40,225 --> 00:07:43,415
That would be much too direct.

123
00:07:43,656 --> 00:07:45,011
Is the bar close?

124
00:07:45,223 --> 00:07:47,543
Yeah, let me draw you a map.

125
00:07:47,693 --> 00:07:50,556
Ahh... Forget it. I need to
go back to the gym anyway.

126
00:07:53,770 --> 00:07:55,800
How about...

127
00:08:00,113 --> 00:08:02,473
her husband?

128
00:08:02,910 --> 00:08:04,808
Her husband died,

129
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:07,123
and she lives alone with Mayu-chan.

130
00:08:07,309 --> 00:08:10,849
They live around Ohkubo.

131
00:08:14,323 --> 00:08:15,773
I didn't ask you that...

132
00:08:16,129 --> 00:08:18,189
I asked you nothing!

133
00:08:54,009 --> 00:08:55,299
Here....

134
00:08:55,477 --> 00:08:56,824
Bon apetit.

135
00:08:56,996 --> 00:09:00,261
Sorry for troubling you so much.

136
00:09:00,406 --> 00:09:02,576
No... Not at all.

137
00:09:08,203 --> 00:09:10,473
It's great!

138
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:14,385
I want to go cheer
for you at a boxing event.

139
00:09:14,638 --> 00:09:15,568
Really?

140
00:09:15,746 --> 00:09:17,286
Then, I'll invite you.

141
00:09:17,355 --> 00:09:20,391
Still, coming alone
would be a tad awkward,

142
00:09:20,416 --> 00:09:21,896
so come with your mother.

143
00:09:21,921 --> 00:09:23,834
- All the better.
- Give it a rest.

144
00:09:24,030 --> 00:09:26,060
- Uhh?!
- Why, you can't?

145
00:09:26,547 --> 00:09:28,108
We'll come to cheer for you.

146
00:09:28,133 --> 00:09:30,963
But we'll pay our
tickets like everyone else.

147
00:09:33,846 --> 00:09:37,158
If I win the next bout, I'll
treat you two to some katsudon.

148
00:09:37,183 --> 00:09:38,306
I'll have to!

149
00:09:38,331 --> 00:09:39,301
You must win.

150
00:09:39,326 --> 00:09:40,409
It's a promise.

151
00:09:40,883 --> 00:09:42,555
Then, here's my finger.

152
00:09:42,802 --> 00:09:47,372
"It's a promise, if you break it,
eat a thousand needles."

153
00:09:47,397 --> 00:09:49,177
"It's a promise!"

154
00:09:55,976 --> 00:09:58,626
Here is my number.

155
00:09:59,260 --> 00:10:02,050
Ahh... Yes.

156
00:10:13,703 --> 00:10:17,433
When the bout is announced,
you can call me at this number.

157
00:10:27,933 --> 00:10:30,137
Master. How about Akemi-san's?

158
00:10:30,497 --> 00:10:32,687
Making it.

159
00:10:41,174 --> 00:10:42,520
Wow!

160
00:11:06,751 --> 00:11:08,565
Isn't it amazing?

161
00:11:20,932 --> 00:11:24,348
~ Japan's 4th Ranked Lightweight ~
Samejima Toru

162
00:11:24,348 --> 00:11:26,884
~ Lightweight ~
Kawada Katsutoshi

163
00:11:26,884 --> 00:11:29,864
~ Samejima Promises
3rd Round KO of Kawada ~

164
00:11:46,376 --> 00:11:49,006
Can I have some water?

165
00:11:56,543 --> 00:11:58,643
Komichi-san...

166
00:11:59,104 --> 00:12:02,014
He's been working so hard,

167
00:12:02,329 --> 00:12:05,669
I'd hate to show him my B-game.

168
00:12:09,003 --> 00:12:11,833
I was...

169
00:12:13,460 --> 00:12:16,770
thinking about quitting my job.

170
00:12:17,543 --> 00:12:21,369
It's just that, if I don't give it my all,
winning will not be easy.

171
00:12:24,197 --> 00:12:26,997
You can be quite
dense sometimes...

172
00:12:27,953 --> 00:12:29,947
Right?!

173
00:12:30,355 --> 00:12:32,595
Can't say I'm not.

174
00:12:32,947 --> 00:12:35,591
But I'm putting everything
on the line for this bout.

175
00:12:35,883 --> 00:12:38,793
It could very well be my last chance.

176
00:12:39,521 --> 00:12:40,758
Want to have breakfast?

177
00:12:40,783 --> 00:12:43,556
I need to make up my mind.

178
00:12:43,889 --> 00:12:47,468
Otherwise, I'll never be able
to escape from this situation.

179
00:12:47,823 --> 00:12:53,783
I think I'd just keep stalling
until I can't do this anymore.

180
00:12:58,457 --> 00:13:01,930
Everyone thinks I
will get knocked out,

181
00:13:02,369 --> 00:13:05,218
but I will make sure it doesn't happen.

182
00:13:05,476 --> 00:13:07,538
I will keep my guard
up until the middle portion,

183
00:13:07,563 --> 00:13:11,851
and then go at him with a
killer punch near the end.

184
00:13:16,818 --> 00:13:18,578
I reserved a seat for you.

185
00:13:18,603 --> 00:13:22,153
I'll wait for you here.

186
00:13:23,826 --> 00:13:27,241
I'll open earlier,
and will be waiting for you.

187
00:13:27,266 --> 00:13:30,575
Give it to someone else.

188
00:13:31,166 --> 00:13:33,556
Should I?

189
00:13:37,846 --> 00:13:39,571
By the way...

190
00:13:39,596 --> 00:13:42,266
Don't laugh and just listen.

191
00:13:43,000 --> 00:13:43,645
Yeah.

192
00:13:45,858 --> 00:13:47,889
You know...

193
00:13:48,293 --> 00:13:53,063
I'm thinking of proposing
to Akemi-san on the ring.

194
00:13:57,713 --> 00:14:00,173
Like Rocky did.

195
00:14:12,602 --> 00:14:16,062
They lure you somewhere
and then ask you to sign.

196
00:14:16,087 --> 00:14:17,522
Should we go see that?

197
00:14:17,547 --> 00:14:18,243
Uh?

198
00:14:18,268 --> 00:14:20,423
Forget that!

199
00:14:20,448 --> 00:14:21,350
But, you know?

200
00:14:21,375 --> 00:14:24,048
Samejima, if he wins this,
he'll get a title shot.

201
00:14:24,073 --> 00:14:25,948
Kawada has no chances of winning.

202
00:14:25,973 --> 00:14:27,961
That's for sure.
Against Samejima, it's only natural.

203
00:14:27,986 --> 00:14:29,447
But, I hear they're showing it
live on TV?

204
00:14:29,472 --> 00:14:31,740
Yeah... It's a big chance for Kawada.

205
00:14:31,765 --> 00:14:34,191
Excuse me...
Want another bottle of this?

206
00:14:34,216 --> 00:14:35,628
- Yeah.
- Shochu?

207
00:14:35,653 --> 00:14:37,323
- Sure.
- All right.

208
00:14:38,659 --> 00:14:41,424
But if he loses, Kawada
might even consider retiring.

209
00:14:41,449 --> 00:14:47,141
- Will he go out with a bang?
- Might be what he's looking for.

210
00:15:10,557 --> 00:15:12,647
Good evening.

211
00:15:13,666 --> 00:15:15,186
Come on in.

212
00:15:17,106 --> 00:15:20,446
No customers tonight?

213
00:15:21,076 --> 00:15:22,703
Yeah...

214
00:15:23,493 --> 00:15:25,383
Is Mayu-chan home?

215
00:15:25,515 --> 00:15:28,155
She's sleeping at a friend's.

216
00:15:28,706 --> 00:15:31,336
She's so excited.

217
00:15:32,913 --> 00:15:36,872
Her friend's got
really great parents,

218
00:15:37,262 --> 00:15:40,281
and lacks nothing.

219
00:15:40,921 --> 00:15:42,211
Bourbon on the rocks.

220
00:15:42,236 --> 00:15:43,616
Sure.

221
00:15:52,422 --> 00:15:55,722
Sometimes, I feel like all
this is getting tiresome, Master.

222
00:15:58,413 --> 00:16:01,202
Mayu keeps growing,

223
00:16:01,227 --> 00:16:04,504
and her tuition is no laughing matter.

224
00:16:05,067 --> 00:16:09,617
And I'm not getting
any younger myself.

225
00:16:11,789 --> 00:16:13,131
You know, Kat-chan?

226
00:16:13,156 --> 00:16:18,925
He quit his job, saying he
wanted to focus on training.

227
00:16:19,518 --> 00:16:23,688
I wonder what he plans
to do in case he loses.

228
00:16:23,713 --> 00:16:28,333
And whether he's even
thinking about his future...

229
00:16:31,152 --> 00:16:32,972
To him,

230
00:16:33,339 --> 00:16:37,125
boxing must be the
most important thing in his life?!

231
00:16:37,602 --> 00:16:39,475
Now, it has to be.

232
00:16:40,044 --> 00:16:42,707
But give him some time.

233
00:16:43,126 --> 00:16:46,666
See how Mayu-chan listens to him?

234
00:16:46,803 --> 00:16:49,785
That's because she doesn't
remember her father's face,

235
00:16:49,810 --> 00:16:53,160
so she might feel affinity
for a gentle man like him.

236
00:16:59,403 --> 00:17:02,432
You'll go support him, right?

237
00:17:04,086 --> 00:17:06,896
Don't know.

238
00:17:10,580 --> 00:17:12,506
Isn't this oolong tea?

239
00:17:13,250 --> 00:17:14,566
That's a relief.

240
00:17:15,586 --> 00:17:17,842
You still remember how it tastes like.

241
00:17:17,867 --> 00:17:20,887
Master, give it a rest!

242
00:17:21,060 --> 00:17:24,510
Go see Kat-chan's fight, will you?

243
00:17:36,438 --> 00:17:38,058
All you need in this world...

244
00:17:38,083 --> 00:17:41,003
is two people liking each other.

245
00:17:55,623 --> 00:17:57,343
So....

246
00:17:58,597 --> 00:18:00,957
Win for us and let's
go have some katsudon.

247
00:18:06,906 --> 00:18:10,447
Golden Rookie Samejima is taking his
first step along the path to legendary status.

248
00:18:10,472 --> 00:18:12,294
It is a fight even his opponent, Kawada,
had long been looking forward to.

249
00:18:12,319 --> 00:18:14,789
Here's the gong starting our first round.

250
00:19:05,943 --> 00:19:06,824
Kawada on the offensive!

251
00:19:06,849 --> 00:19:09,951
Kawada is starting
to take the initiative.

252
00:19:46,767 --> 00:19:48,807
- Down!
- Kat-chan!

253
00:19:49,056 --> 00:19:51,056
1.... 2....

254
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:53,930
3..... 4....

255
00:19:58,352 --> 00:19:59,642
Box!

256
00:20:23,513 --> 00:20:25,273
This way.

257
00:21:23,699 --> 00:21:25,619
You gave your best.

258
00:21:32,949 --> 00:21:38,963
Everyone, thank you for
supporting me all this time.

259
00:21:40,243 --> 00:21:43,383
Here... Kat-chan.
Good job.

260
00:21:43,863 --> 00:21:45,055
Cheers!

261
00:21:45,139 --> 00:21:46,809
Cheers!

262
00:21:55,985 --> 00:21:58,408
Master.
Katsudon for me.

263
00:21:58,433 --> 00:21:59,263
Mayu!

264
00:21:59,366 --> 00:22:01,376
I'm hungry.

265
00:22:01,503 --> 00:22:02,773
Is it all right with you?

266
00:22:04,706 --> 00:22:06,586
Master.
Katsudon for three.

267
00:22:06,703 --> 00:22:08,053
Coming!

268
00:22:09,433 --> 00:22:13,193
Sorry for not keeping my promise.

269
00:22:13,587 --> 00:22:15,457
You didn't lose.

270
00:22:15,482 --> 00:22:17,312
We know that.

271
00:22:18,250 --> 00:22:19,320
Right, Mom?

272
00:22:24,490 --> 00:22:26,030
Still hurts?

273
00:22:28,105 --> 00:22:29,911
This is nothing.

274
00:22:29,936 --> 00:22:32,356
Don't tell me you're gonna cry?

275
00:22:43,374 --> 00:22:44,583
Master...

276
00:22:45,876 --> 00:22:47,196
This...

277
00:22:47,575 --> 00:22:51,770
<i>(*deep-fried pork part of katsudon)</i>
Sadly, I ran out of tonkatsu*, so...

278
00:22:59,223 --> 00:23:05,514
<i>(*Donburi with chicken and eggs, but
literally means "parents-and-child" donburi)</i>
Oyakodon*.

279
00:23:08,502 --> 00:23:11,902
~ to be continued ~

280
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:30,441
Thank you for waiting.

281
00:23:30,660 --> 00:23:33,365
Because the meat will get
cooked even more at the end,

282
00:23:33,390 --> 00:23:35,725
turn it off a little earlier while frying.

283
00:23:35,750 --> 00:23:38,240
Always be careful not to overcook it.

284
00:23:38,270 --> 00:23:41,451
So, here's the recipe
for oyakodon as well.

285
00:23:41,476 --> 00:23:43,585
Ohh.... We have no time?!

286
00:23:43,610 --> 00:23:46,220
We became parents and child.

287
00:23:46,245 --> 00:23:47,554
Good night everyone!

288
00:23:47,579 --> 00:23:50,573
Good night.

